The paper deals with capsule networks, which are primarily used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object recognition. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and routing algorithms, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of group-equivariant convolutions, which are commonly used in neural networks for tasks such as natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of parameter-sharing and the efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
